{
  "text": "In [CITATION_1] , Jaschke et al. have proposed the Trias that also computes closed 3-sets in a ternary relation. It basically relies on formal concept computation on two different binary relations. To compute all closed n-sets on a relation R \u2286 D 1 . The set B stands for a relation which is not fully connected (i.e., there are false values in its Boolean representation). Thus, in a second step, Trias computes formal concepts in the relation generated by B and checks if the obtained formal concepts are closed w.r.t. D",
